.TH "textsearch_register" 9 "textsearch_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
textsearch_register \- register a textsearch module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" textsearch_register
.BI "(struct ts_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ops" 12
operations lookup table
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be called by textsearch modules to announce
their presence. The specified &\fIops\fP must have name set to a
unique identifier and the callbacks \fBfind\fP, \fBinit\fP, \fBget_pattern\fP,
and \fBget_pattern_len\fP must be implemented.

Returns 0 or -EEXISTS if another module has already registered
with same name.
